# System Design

## Purpose

System design is a first-class deliverable in this project — it demonstrates the ability to reason about architecture before writing code. Every service must be designed on paper before implementation starts.

## Where docs live

```
docs/
├── system-design/
│   ├── overview.md           ← full system diagram and service map
│   ├── upload-flow.md        ← end-to-end flow: browser → uploader-api → storage
│   ├── stream-flow.md        ← end-to-end flow: browser → watcher-api → player
│   ├── capacity.md           ← storage estimates, bandwidth, concurrency limits
│   └── [FILL: add one doc per major design area]
└── adr/
    ├── 001-streaming-protocol.md
    ├── 002-cpp-framework.md
    └── [FILL: one ADR per architectural decision]
```

## What each system design doc must cover

1. **What problem it solves** — one paragraph, no jargon
2. **Components involved** — list all services, storage, and external systems
3. **Data flow** — step-by-step, numbered, with the happy path and at least one failure case
4. **Interfaces** — how components talk to each other (HTTP, file system, shared volume, etc.)
5. **Open questions** — what is still undecided and needs an ADR

## ADR Format

Each `docs/adr/NNN-title.md` must follow this structure:

```markdown
# NNN — Decision Title

**Date**: YYYY-MM-DD
**Status**: Proposed | Accepted | Superseded by ADR-NNN

## Context
What is the problem? Why is a decision needed now?

## Options Considered
- Option A: description + tradeoffs
- Option B: description + tradeoffs
- Option C: description + tradeoffs

## Decision
Which option was chosen and why.

## Consequences
What does this decision make easier? What does it make harder?
```

